    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="334"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d334">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1479a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">White</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-15T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 15, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A commission composed of the American Minister, Mr. Sullivan, Ex-Governor Fort of
                    New Jersey and Mr. Charles Cogswell Smith, <pb facs="0365" n="249"
                        xml:id="pg_249"/> attorney-at-law, of New Hampshire, left Santiago, Cuba,
                    today proceeding on board U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Prairie</hi> first to
                    Puerto Plata and thence to Santo Domingo City. Arrange for customs facilities
                    for commission, requesting such in the name of the Government of the United
                    States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
